FT  23 APR 94 / Finance and the Family: Investors benefit
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The government's belated concession on capital gains tax indexation has some
unexpected side effects. The change in the basis of calculating relief means
that some investors will be better off than they would have been before the
Budget rule change.
Unusually, you can use up part of your annual CGT exemption in 1993-94, even
if your indexation losses in that year exceed your gains. Normally, losses
have to be offset against profits before taking account of the exemption.
