<HEADLINE>
FT  23 APR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Equity futures and options trading
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTINE BUCKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Nervousness subsided in the recently volatile equity derivatives and the
June FT-SE contract traded in a narrow range, writes Christine Buckley.
But one broker's head of derivatives warned that the confident performance
may just be a bear market bounce.
June traded at a premium to cash for most of the session, marking an
intraday high of 3,154 although its close at 3,140 trailed the fair-value
premium by about a couple of points.
Volume was subdued at 11,352 contracts while options activity was dull at
29,058 lots.
