<HEADLINE>
FT  23 APR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Lasmo interest
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Takeover speculation continued to surround Lasmo with analysts pointing to
Atlantic Richfield as a likely bidder. The speculation prompted heavy
turnover with the ordinary shares trading 15m, the new 'nil paid' seeing
volume of 13m and active volume in traded options. The shares closed 2 up at
147p.
Mr Simon Flowers, oil analyst with NatWest, argued that the re-rating had
been driven by the recent rights issue but the rights issue had 'forced the
market to have a major review of Lasmo as an investment'. Both Elf and
British Gas have been targeted as potential predators but both are believed
to be preoccupied with their own concerns.
