<HEADLINE>
FT  23 APR 94 / Ex-defence chief jailed for year
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A former senior defence official who took thousands of pounds in
'backhanders' over armaments contracts was jailed for a year yesterday at
Southwark Crown Court.
Mr Trevelyan, of Rowley Regis, West Midlands - who headed the Ministry of
Defence's light armoured engineering systems - was convicted of four counts
of corruption involving a total of Pounds 8,652 and one charge of attempted
corruption, which could have netted him a further Pounds 28,580.
Mr David Oliver, of Camberley, Surrey, managing director of defence agents
Imvec, was fined Pounds 4,000 after being found guilty of corruptly paying
Mr Trevelyan, a close friend, Pounds 2,000 for a report on armoured
vehicles.
