<HEADLINE>
FT  22 APR 94 / World Stock Markets: S Africa ends lower
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Johannesburg ended a quiet day lower with investors reluctant to commit
themselves less than a week before the elections. The weakness of the gold
price and a firmer financial rand added to the hesitant tone.
The overall index finished 8 softer at 5,037 and golds fell 23 to 1,860, but
industrials managed a gain of 3 to 5,963.
De Beers ended 50 cents lower at R107 and JCI fell R1 to R91. Richemont
reversed small early gains to lose 50 cents to R41, but substantial gains in
industrials were registered for Iscor, which added 7 cents to R3.27 and
Malbak, up 65 cents to R18.90.
</TEXT>
