FT  22 APR 94 / International Capital Markets: Warrant on Swedish stocks is
launched
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SG Warburg Global Equity Derivatives has launched its first issue of covered
warrants on a basket of Swedish stocks.
The American-style call warrants are on a basket made up of 50 shares in
ASEA, 70 in Ericsson, 80 in Investor, 20 in SSAB and 40 in Volvo. The value
of one basket is approximately SKr104,000. One thousand warrants control one
basket, and the approximate issue price per warrant is SKr16.3.
The issue was targeted on the back of research by Swedish stockbroking firm
Haglof and Ponsbach. In December, SG Warburg agreed to buy the research and
institutional sales business of Haglof and Ponsbach from Gota Bank.
Salomon Brothers has launched its second issue of warrants on the
recently-introduced 30-year German government bond. The warrants have a
one-year life.
The number of UK equity warrant issues has grown by 13 per cent, to 224 from
198, since the start of the year, according to the McHattie Group's latest
warrants directory.
