   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The liberalisation of stock market commissions on Japanese transactions of
more than Y1bn has not hurt brokers, according to the Japan Securities
Dealers' Association, Reuter reports from Tokyo.
The association said there were not many transactions of more than Y1bn in
